📊 CONFIDENCE SCORING SYSTEM
Every recommendation includes a confidence score with 4 components:
json{
  "overall": 82,
  "reasoning_quality": 90,
  "data_completeness": 85,
  "user_alignment": 75
}
Reasoning Quality (0-100)

How solid is the logic?
Are there clear trade-offs?
Is the recommendation defensible?
Range: 90-100 (math is clear) to 60-70 (multiple valid approaches)

Data Completeness (0-100)

Do we have all the data we need?
Is portfolio data fresh? (<24 hours = 95%)
Do we know user's tax bracket? (missing = -10%)
Is there missing cost basis? (-15%)
Range: 95-100 (complete data) to 60-70 (several gaps)

User Alignment (0-100)

Does this match user's goals/values?
Does it match their decision patterns?
Have they rejected similar moves before? (-20%)
Have they consistently executed this type of move? (+10%)
Range: 95-100 (perfect fit) to 50-60 (misaligned)

Overall = Weighted average of the three

Typical range: 60-90%
<60% = "This recommendation isn't ready yet"
80%+ = "High confidence, safe to recommend"


🚀 QUICK START FOR DEVELOPERS
To implement Fin agents:

Read 04_user_context_file_schema.md - Understand the data structure
Read 05_implementation_guide.md - Follow step-by-step
Review 01, 02, 03 agent prompts - Understand the logic
Set up Docker Compose - Get Ollama running locally
Load system prompts - Store in database or files
Test with sample context - Verify agent responses
Build frontend - Display recommendations with voting
Integrate API connections - Alpaca, Plaid, Finnhub
Deploy & monitor - Track recommendation quality


❓ FAQ
Q: Why three separate agents instead of one?
A: Specialization enables better recommendations. Each agent has domain expertise and tailored reasoning.
Q: What if user context is incomplete?
A: Agents use web search to fill gaps. They also note uncertainty in confidence scores.
Q: How do agents learn from user feedback?
A: After each vote (accept/reject), the User Context File is updated. Next conversation uses updated patterns.
Q: Can agents directly communicate with each other?
A: No, but they coordinate through the shared User Context File. Debt Agent sees Investment Agent notes, etc.
Q: What LLM should we use?
A: Mistral 7B or Llama 2 13B work well. Both fit in ~7-13GB memory, support long context windows (32K tokens).
Q: How are API credentials secured?
A: Encrypted at rest (AES-256) in database. Decrypted only when making API calls. Never shown to user after initial entry.
Q: What if Ollama is offline?
A: Fin degrades gracefully. Can't generate new recommendations, but can display past ones and historical data.

